00:15:18,184 --> 00:15:19,284
What? This?

263
00:15:19,320 --> 00:15:20,934
I just wanted to
try out a new look.

264
00:15:22,688 --> 00:15:24,040
You like?

265
00:15:24,669 --> 00:15:25,371
Hmm.

266
00:15:25,742 --> 00:15:28,999
Well, in that case, have you
seen anypony suspicious around?

267
00:15:29,484 --> 00:15:30,731
Uh, nope.

268
00:15:35,071 --> 00:15:35,978
Princess Twilight!

269
00:15:36,140 --> 00:15:38,136
The gazebo has been
turned into solid crystal

270
00:15:38,275 --> 00:15:40,807
and two ponies are now
trapped inside its walls!

271
00:15:47,449 --> 00:15:48,325
Hoo!

272
00:15:48,460 --> 00:15:52,074
No! I made a promise to Rarity
to keep this to myself.

273
00:15:52,415 --> 00:15:53,104
Hoo!

274
00:15:54,392 --> 00:15:57,274
But you're right
Owlowiscious, I have to tell.

275
00:15:57,769 --> 00:16:01,010
And once I do, I can forget
Rarity thinking of me

276
00:16:01,026 --> 00:16:02,755
as her most supportive friend.

277
00:16:03,769 --> 00:16:07,486
I can forget Rarity thinking
of me as a friend at all.

278
00:16:17,793 --> 00:16:19,008
I can't do it.

279
00:16:20,316 --> 00:16:22,589
I promised I'd keep all of
this between the three of us.

280
00:16:23,246 --> 00:16:24,191
Hoo!

281
00:16:24,860 --> 00:16:27,026
Of course, it's weird
that she meant me, her,

282
00:16:27,034 --> 00:16:28,150
and the spell book, but--

283
00:16:29,155 --> 00:16:31,065
The spell book! Of course!

284
00:16:31,373 --> 00:16:32,675
If I can get it away from her,

285
00:16:32,891 --> 00:16:34,891
I bet she won't be able
to use its magic anymore.

286
00:16:36,132 --> 00:16:38,360
<i>Oh, come on! It's</i>
<i>the perfect plan.</i>

287
00:16:39,176 --> 00:16:41,890
I just have to figure
out which way she went.

288
00:16:42,023 --> 00:16:43,340
<i>I can't see!</i>

289
00:16:49,260 --> 00:16:51,543
I'm thinking she's
headed this way.

290
00:17:08,376 --> 00:17:09,566
What do you think
you're doing?

291
00:17:10,321 --> 00:17:15,112
Me? I was just uh, basking
in your creative radiance.

292
00:17:16,401 --> 00:17:19,810
Oh, Spike, you do say
the nicest things!

293
00:17:20,577 --> 00:17:21,174
Thanks.

294
00:17:21,777 --> 00:17:23,449
Now where was I?

295
00:17:27,422 --> 00:17:28,105
Oh, yes!

296
00:17:28,546 --> 00:17:31,680
Gold-plated roof-tops
for everypony!

297
00:17:31,980 --> 00:17:34,048
Hoo! Hoo! Hoo!

298
00:17:40,056 --> 00:17:40,803
Spike!

299
00:17:44,729 --> 00:17:46,864
I have just had the
most marvellous idea!

300
00:17:50,552 --> 00:17:53,125
Of course you have;
you're Rarity.

301
00:17:54,364 --> 00:17:56,669
My work here in Ponyville
is nearly complete.

302
00:17:57,196 --> 00:17:59,947
Don't you think it's time
the rest of Equestria

303
00:17:59,962 --> 00:18:01,840
benefited from my
creative vision?

304
00:18:02,624 --> 00:18:03,781
Absolutely!

305
00:18:05,748 --> 00:18:07,600
I'm thinking we go by chariot.

306
00:18:07,871 --> 00:18:10,803
Or as everyone will soon
be calling them, "Rariot".

307
00:18:13,006 --> 00:18:15,342
Oh, yeah! We should
definitely go by--

308
00:18:19,968 --> 00:18:22,714
How...how did you do that?

309
00:18:23,221 --> 00:18:24,960
Why, whatever do you mean?

310
00:18:25,334 --> 00:18:28,232
The book. It's... I
mean... you don't...

311
00:18:28,915 --> 00:18:30,000
It's gone.

312
00:18:30,216 --> 00:18:31,240
The book is gone.

313
00:18:31,469 --> 00:18:32,115
Gone?

314
00:18:32,370 --> 00:18:33,424
Why it's right there.

315
00:18:35,363 --> 00:18:37,106
I need my book, Spike!

316
00:18:37,400 --> 00:18:39,026
What have you done
with my book?

317
00:18:40,641 --> 00:18:42,807
Why would I do anything
with your book?

318
00:18:43,057 --> 00:18:44,029
We're friends.

319
00:18:44,392 --> 00:18:46,720
It was probably the owl!

320
00:18:48,124 --> 00:18:48,872
Hoo!

321
00:18:49,701 --> 00:18:53,459
But, wait, I don't seem
to need it anymore, do I?

322
00:18:54,255 --> 00:18:56,087
Yes! Yes!

323
00:18:56,636 --> 00:18:59,469
I can feel its magic
flowing within me now.

324
00:18:59,847 --> 00:19:03,024
I'm so excited!
I'm so excited!

325
00:19:03,613 --> 00:19:04,798
I'm so scared.

326
00:19:05,061 --> 00:19:06,647
<i>Oh, the places</i>
<i>we'll go, Spike.</i>

327
00:19:07,028 --> 00:19:07,935
Manehattan.

328
00:19:08,062 --> 00:19:09,063
Phillydelphia.

329
00:19:09,211 --> 00:19:10,107
Canterlot.

330
00:19:10,768 --> 00:19:12,448
And there you'll
be by my side.

331
00:19:12,583 --> 00:19:14,499
Just as you've always
been here in Ponyville.

332
00:19:14,565 --> 00:19:17,157
Your constant praise and
adoration driving me

333
00:19:17,164 --> 00:19:18,349
to even greater heights

334
00:19:18,490 --> 00:19:20,265
until there isn't an
inch of Equestria

335
00:19:20,273 --> 00:19:22,115
that hasn't been
utterly transformed

336
00:19:22,200 --> 00:19:25,326
by my creative genius!

337
00:19:31,732 --> 00:19:32,325
No!

338
00:19:33,153 --> 00:19:34,868
What did you say?

339
00:19:35,153 --> 00:19:36,206
I said, "No!"

340
00:19:36,739 --> 00:19:37,828
You've been changing things,

341
00:19:37,838 --> 00:19:39,182
but you haven't been
making them better.

342
00:19:39,861 --> 00:19:41,964
I should have told you the
truth at the very beginning,

343
00:19:42,076 --> 00:19:42,626
but I didn't

344
00:19:42,638 --> 00:19:44,579
because I was trying to be
a supportive friend.

345
00:19:46,027 --> 00:19:50,124
But instead I let you
become something awful.

346
00:19:51,457 --> 00:19:52,208
Awful?

347
00:20:03,992 --> 00:20:05,326
What happened?

348
00:20:05,791 --> 00:20:07,892
Rarity, you're OK?

349
00:20:08,384 --> 00:20:10,569
I...I think so.

350
00:20:11,898 --> 00:20:14,788
Though by the looks of it,
something quite terrifying

351
00:20:14,798 --> 00:20:16,552
has happened to Ponyville.

352
00:20:17,736 --> 00:20:18,760
You happened.

353
00:20:19,278 --> 00:20:20,144
Me?

354
00:20:21,574 --> 00:20:23,564
The last part of the spell!

355
00:20:24,526 --> 00:20:26,846
"Only when true
words are spoken,

356
00:20:26,856 --> 00:20:29,539
will you finally be set free."

357
00:20:31,106 --> 00:20:32,228
The spell took over you

358
00:20:32,234 --> 00:20:34,195
and you wanted to change
everything in Equestria.

359
00:20:34,780 --> 00:20:37,399
I was afraid to tell you
how I really felt about it,

360
00:20:37,791 --> 00:20:40,462
but then I, I told
you the truth.

361
00:20:41,295 --> 00:20:45,034
Dearest Spike, you should never
be afraid to tell me the truth.

362
00:20:45,354 --> 00:20:46,944
We're friends, remember?

363
00:20:50,645 --> 00:20:52,597
<i>Today I learned how important it is</i>

364
00:20:52,626 --> 00:20:54,009
<i>to be honest with your friends</i>

365
00:20:54,019 --> 00:20:55,283
<i>when they're doing something</i>

366
00:20:55,293 --> 00:20:56,708
<i>that you don't think is right.</i>

367
00:20:56,997 --> 00:20:59,190
A true friend knows
that you're speaking up

368
00:20:59,340 --> 00:21:00,612
because you care about them.

369
00:21:01,494 --> 00:21:02,304
Spike!

370
00:21:02,700 --> 00:21:07,246
Never, ever, ever take another
book out of the library

371
00:21:07,365 --> 00:21:09,453
at the Castle without asking.

372
00:21:09,695 --> 00:21:11,229
Princess Cadance
and Princess Luna

373
00:21:11,235 --> 00:21:14,005
have much better things to do
than help me clean up Ponyville.

374
00:21:16,803 --> 00:21:18,565
Do you have any idea how
hard it was to reverse

375
00:21:18,575 --> 00:21:19,910
that much dark magic?

376
00:21:22,173 --> 00:21:23,451
You don't look so good.

377
00:21:24,913 --> 00:21:25,592
What?

378
00:21:25,838 --> 00:21:27,010
I'm just being honest.

379
00:21:27,166 --> 00:21:28,682
It's what good friends do.

